<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id0df71267-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="priorProvisions" id="id0df71268-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prior Provisions</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">A prior <ref href="/us/pl/102/259/s10">section 10 of Pub. L. 102–259</ref> was renumbered section 12 and is classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t20/s5608">section 5608 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id0df71269-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2019—Subsec. (b). <ref href="/us/pl/116/94">Pub. L. 116–94</ref> substituted “National Center” for “Institute”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1998—Subsec. (b). <ref href="/us/pl/105/277">Pub. L. 105–277</ref> inserted before period at end “, including not to exceed $1,000 annually for official reception and representation expenses”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
